        <updated>2021-08-10T11:37:50.000Z</updated>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>钣金的晶粒方向就是金属延展的方向，RD；</p>
<p><img src="https://Aero-Jack.github.io/post-images/1628595718324.png" alt="" loading="lazy"><br>
因此钣金在折弯的时候，折弯的bend line/heel line/折弯线是垂直于晶粒方向的。你可以想想晶粒是一条线，类似于复合材料，垂直于fiber不会折断；平行于fiber的话，反而fiber是分开的。<br>
<img src="https://Aero-Jack.github.io/post-images/1628595741993.png" alt="" loading="lazy"><br>
下图垂直于晶粒方向，不会又断裂；平行于晶粒方向就有可能产生断裂<br>
<img src="https://Aero-Jack.github.io/post-images/1628595751833.png" alt="" loading="lazy"><br>
L或者RD都是晶粒方向，LT是宽度方向，ST就是厚度方向。LT,ST都是扩展的方向。<br>
<img src="https://Aero-Jack.github.io/post-images/1628595776612.png" alt="" loading="lazy"><br>
这里可以看到ST,LT以及L<br>
for rectangular hand forgings, the call-out for hand forgings is in this order: Short transverse [ST], (Thickness), Long transverse [LT], (width) and finally the Longitudinal [L] (length).<br>
<img src="https://Aero-Jack.github.io/post-images/1628595782737.png" alt="" loading="lazy"><br>
这里指明出来，对于折弯的时候，如何选对方向。垂直于晶粒方向最好。<br>
<img src="https://Aero-Jack.github.io/post-images/1628595790080.png" alt="" loading="lazy"></p>
